Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.58,0:00:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The macrocosm operates with a certain law and rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.05,0:00:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There floats a planet called Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.70,0:00:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,On it, in the corner of an island nation called Japan, there is me... But for what purpose? {unsure: その中の日本という 島国の一隅で 私は今何をしようとしているのか･･･}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.06,0:00:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To fight the battle for the Common Path \Nand bring happiness and peace to people
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.90,0:00:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a battle against the demons
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.08,0:01:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that destroy the rhythm of life \Nand prevent us from living a healthy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A battle against the evil that does not show itself, not even for a moment. {probably means "you can't fight it with fists, it doesn't have a physical form"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.37,0:01:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I am declaring a battle on demons that pervade society on this earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.85,0:01:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One we can't afford to lose. \NOne we must win at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.18,0:01:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Nam Myoho Renge Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.74,0:01:27.69,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,New Year's Day, 1948.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.69,0:01:34.86,Sign,,0,0,0,,New Year's Day, 1948 \NSoka Gakkai Headquarters {1948年(昭和23年)元旦。学会本部}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.69,0:01:30.92,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Toda and a few other executives conducted the first service
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.92,0:01:34.86,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,at the new Soka Gakkai headquarters, \NNihon Shogakkan office in Nishi-Kanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.86,0:01:42.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,Offering Sake {御造酒 - seems to be some specific offering used in nichiren buddhism}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.72,0:01:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy New Year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.93,0:01:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Happy New Year!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.93,0:01:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy New Year, Sensei. I hope we'll keep doing what we're doing this year as well. {aikawarazu = as always, without change}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.96,0:01:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.01,0:01:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we'll be in trouble if we just keep doing our usual things this year. Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.71,0:02:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,By sticking to the same work as last year, \Nwe'll just stifle the Common Path. {/lead ... to stagnation}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.49,0:02:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean to say you'll keep fidgeting during lectures this year, Harayama-kun? {lit: moving restlessly - no clue what he means, assuming harayama is inattentive or something}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishima-kun will keep grunting, \NKonishi-kun will keep sulking,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Seki-kun will keep \Nlooking pale and thoughtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.06,0:02:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's what worries me the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.26,0:02:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The reconstruction of the Society \Nturns three this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.93,0:02:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that you will make full use of your strengths,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.99,0:02:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and fulfill your missionary mission wonderfully with a strong and staunch faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we need this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.27,0:02:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll all have to undergo a drastic change.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.87,0:02:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you all think that you've done well in your endeavors last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.70,0:02:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, our activity \Nwas mostly inertia-driven.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.95,0:02:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For me, it was giving lectures \Nand going to roundtable discussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.15,0:02:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But outside that, little to no educational work was undertaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When an organization becomes more orderly, inertia among executives inevitably begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.57,0:03:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But can't notice it ourselves. We just think that we're still doing a good job, like before. {like last year/as always}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.37,0:03:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We settle for this "like before" as "good enough." \NThat's the root of stagnation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.29,0:03:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive my slip-up earlier, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.10,0:03:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to evolving with you this year, \Nand welcome any change.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.65,0:03:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.80,0:03:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I understand it very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.06,0:03:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Does everyone else understand it too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.24,0:03:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.24,0:03:25.41,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.41,0:03:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My oh my. I'm sorry for talking to you \Nso sternly on the New Year's Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.04,0:03:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning of the year is supposed to be a joyous occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.71,0:03:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get straight to the festivities. {guess, 早速おとそといこうじゃないか}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.07,0:03:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiyohara-san, will you do us the honor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.05,0:03:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.30,0:03:40.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,Offering Sake
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.84,0:03:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The country of Japan is now taking the first step towards its rebirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.08,0:03:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It means the academia will be reborn as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.70,0:03:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not to say we must branch out into some new field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:03:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Roundtable discussions and lectures are the root of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.47,0:04:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,By carrying out these two activities \Nsystematically and methodically,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we build the foundations for a new Japan\Nthat'll change this society one day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.79,0:04:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow us to create a peaceful world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.20,0:04:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In that sense, rather than trivializing one theory by repeating it a million times,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.34,0:04:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a single roundtable discussion is way more expedient
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.84,0:04:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for releasing the energy needed for the dissemination of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.24,0:04:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make this year a year of training and development of human resources
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.29,0:04:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,through roundtable discussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.91,0:04:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.91,0:04:31.68,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.68,0:04:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.35,0:04:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,everything's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.75,0:04:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Now, everyone, grab yourself a cup, \Nthis is a top-class sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.64,0:04:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.64,0:04:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's raise a toast now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.87,0:04:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.28,0:04:48.65,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Cheers! To you! {itadakimasu}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.65,0:04:52.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,Izu-Shimoda Pass {伊豆・下田街道。}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.11,0:04:53.61,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Early in January, after attending roundtable discussions in various locations,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.61,0:04:56.98,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Toda headed to Shimoda in Izu \Nto preach in the countryside. {lit: regional guidance - think she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.98,0:05:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, whenever I come to Shimoda, \NI can't help thinking about Makiguchi-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.13,0:05:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.01,0:05:13.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's here in Shimoda, where Makiguchi-sensei was apprehended by the police. {/special police squad}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.88,0:05:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He was already 72 years old, \Nso we all tried to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.73,0:05:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, he insisted on attending \Nthe roundtable discussion in Shimoda.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He was an honorable, dignified, and honest teacher with a strong sense of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.40,0:05:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I met him was in the spring of 1920, when I moved to Tokyo from Hokkaido.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.87,0:05:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 20 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:45.30,Top,,0,0,0,,A month or so before that... \NYes, I was still in Yubari district.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.30,0:05:49.28,Top,,0,0,0,,In that snowy coal-mining town of Mayachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:50.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,Hokkaido, Yubari \NMayachi Coal Mine
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.28,0:05:50.41,Top,,0,0,0,,While I was there,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.41,0:05:54.41,Top,,0,0,0,,I worked as an elementary school teacher \Nfor about a year and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.43,0:05:54.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,Mayachi Elementary School {真谷地尋常小學校}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.42,0:05:56.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,Essay \NSubject: "My Hometown"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.81,0:05:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it going, everyone?\NAre you done writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.23,0:06:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.73,0:06:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What was your own hometown like? \NThe Atsuta Village.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.32,0:06:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.31,0:06:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't told you yet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.45,0:06:14.31,Top,,0,0,0,,Well, listen. The Atsuta Village
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.31,0:06:19.33,Top,,0,0,0,,is a small fishing village, facing the Sea of Japan \Nin the northern part of the Ishikari Plain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.33,0:06:19.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Atsuta Village {厚田村}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.33,0:06:22.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,Atsuta River
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.86,0:06:22.34,Top,,0,0,0,,There's nothing there
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.34,0:06:25.56,Top,,0,0,0,,but untouched nature and beautiful scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.34,0:06:28.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,Roulan Coast {comes from ainu word Rueran = a steep slope where the gods pass through; ルーランの奇勝}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.87,0:06:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,During the herring fishing season, the population swells to three times its normal size. {means of people, not herring}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.37,0:06:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The rows and rows of fishermen's huts along the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.32,0:06:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,are a spectacular sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.34,0:06:45.30,Top,,0,0,0,,When I had just graduated from Atsuta Elementary School, {more specifically "advanced course of Atsuta Public Elementary School" but idk what to make of this advanced course}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:47.32,Top,,0,0,0,,I dreamed of pursuing higher education.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.73,0:06:48.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,The house where Toda spent his childhood {戸田が幼少時代を過ごした家}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.32,0:06:50.82,Top,,0,0,0,,But my family was in a tight spot, \Nso I gave up on it and moved to Sapporo
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:53.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,Walking around Sapporo selling miscellaneous goods {札幌市内を雑貨の行商に歩く}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.82,0:06:54.41,Top,,0,0,0,,to work as an indentured servant \Nat a general merchandise store.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.30,0:06:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,While working there, I studied independently and passed the teacher's exam,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming a licensed substitute teacher \Nat this elementary school. And that's how...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.29,0:07:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come to study with you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.98,0:07:13.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But soon after, \Nyoung Toda had to leave Mayuchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.80,0:07:15.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The year he turned 20...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.46,0:07:18.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,You were all good, honest kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.81,0:07:23.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,I have no choice but to leave you. \NForgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.94,0:07:32.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, young Toda resigned his position as an elementary school teacher and set out for Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.34,0:07:37.60,Sign,,0,0,0,,March 1920 \NUeno Station {1920年(大正9年)3月上野駅}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.61,0:07:38.24,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,His first order of business was to earn a living,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.60,0:07:42.60,Sign,,0,0,0,,Mejiro, Takada Ward {目白・高田町}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.24,0:07:42.61,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,so young Toda made rounds of several job agencies, looking for a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.61,0:07:45.24,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,But with the slumping economy \Nand recession raging,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.24,0:07:47.86,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,he wasn't able to land a job anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.86,0:07:50.87,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,And so, when his hope was already waning...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.86,0:07:50.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi's house {牧口家}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.87,0:07:53.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,Letter of introduction {紹介状}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.42,0:07:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,While working at Mayachi Elementary School, \NI wrote a petition to the Minister of Education
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:08:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that if we are to think about the future of Japan, we must value educators in remote areas more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.48,0:08:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never got an answer. {lit: he didn't pick it up}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.77,0:08:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt that I cannot be heard \Nif I stay in the countryside
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.44,0:08:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I have no choice \Nbut to go to work in the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.28,0:08:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering your deep ties to Hokkaido, \NI've decided to stop by here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.59,0:08:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you bring your resume?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.90,0:08:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I have it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.09,0:08:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take a chance on me, sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.38,0:08:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I can turn even the worst performing students \Ninto honor students.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.80,0:08:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I guarantee you won't regret hiring me later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.39,0:08:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.50,0:08:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, you are my last hope. {not really but idk how to put it: I'm counting on you by all means}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.51,0:08:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll help you. {/let's work together}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.55,0:08:53.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Soon after, on the recommendation of Makiguchi, the school's principal,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.50,0:08:57.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda was hired as a teacher \Nat Nishimachi Elementary School in Shitaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.38,0:09:00.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,From then on, \NToda would look up to Makiguchi
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.12,0:09:03.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as his "mentor in life" \Nand serve him for the rest of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.73,0:09:10.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,For the next 23 years, I have served Makiguchi-sensei and fought alongside him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.24,0:09:15.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,for the cause of Common Path, \Nright up until his arrest here in Shimoda.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.91,0:09:19.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,July 6th, 1943 \NSuzaki, Shimoda {1943年(昭和18年)7月6日\N下田・須崎}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.34,0:09:21.39,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi-sensei was the embodiment of the lion spirit that day. {/behaved like a true king of lions ; check notes}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.63,0:09:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is anyone home?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.18,0:09:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.40,0:09:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Shimoda Police Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.40,0:09:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to ask Makiguchi Tsunesaburo, who's staying here, to follow us to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.89,0:09:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?\NWhat is it you want from Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I could understand it if it was Tokyo, \Nbut we're in Shimoda!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.87,0:09:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What could the rural police \Npossibly want with Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.73,0:09:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Makiguchi. \NHow can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.07,0:09:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You are charged with lese-majesty \Nand violation of the Peace Preservation Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.05,0:09:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll know all the details at the station. \NPlease follow us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.33,0:10:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.33,0:10:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.33,0:10:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give me a minute, \NI'll gather my things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.29,0:10:11.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi had been in Izu since July 2nd,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.48,0:10:14.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he held a roundtable discussion at Rendaiji Temple in Shimoda,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.37,0:10:16.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,before arriving here in Suzaki on the 5th.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.53,0:10:20.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although he could feel \Nthe authorities breathing down his neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:25.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi, who had devoted his life to the Common Path, refused to let it frighten him
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.65,0:10:28.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,or bog him down in his fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't repay your kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.99,0:10:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.19,0:10:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.99,0:10:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as I brought you all the way to Suzaki, this happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.49,0:10:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.39,0:10:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.95,0:10:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your time...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.90,0:10:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When you return to Tokyo, \Ngive my regards to Toda-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.04,0:11:03.87,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The military government,\Nwanting to wage war unimpeded,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.11,0:11:08.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi is taken to Shimoda Police Station \Non charges of violating the Peace Preservation Law. {「牧口、治安維持法違反の容疑で下田署に連行される。}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.87,0:11:08.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,saw Soka Gakkai, who rejected to worship Shinto amulets and accept State Shintoism,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.97,0:11:13.21,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,as an anti-national organization and an eyesore, \Nso they cracked down on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.42,0:11:16.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Those who truly loved their country
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.20,0:11:20.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and wished sincerely for the happiness and peace of their people,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.09,0:11:22.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,were labeled as national dissenters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.31,0:11:27.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was a truly deranged time, \Nfilled with irrationality and contradiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.35,0:11:31.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-kun and the other executives \Nare probably going to be arrested too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.85,0:11:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The time has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.45,0:11:38.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,The time has come to fight for our lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.72,0:11:42.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,This battle, which forced a direct confrontation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:47.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,with state power, would probably be remembered as my last remaining example
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.67,0:11:50.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,of admonition to the state. {unsure: 国家権力と真正面から衝突せざるを得ないこの戦いこそ牧口常三郎に最後に残された国家諫暁の実践だといえよう}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.79,0:11:53.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,The time for it has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.75,0:12:01.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,And then, Makiguchi-sensei passed away in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.59,0:12:04.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,Kowtowing is just another word \Nfor "death of human soul."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.78,0:12:09.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,In that sense, Sensei had won the ultimate fight for his religious freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:12.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,He spoke about the theory of goodness \Non his pretrial hearing, {/axiology}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:14.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,he preached Buddha Dharma to the guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.09,0:12:19.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,He kept chanting Nam Myoho Renge Kyo \Nuntil his last moments... {/daimoku}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.73,0:12:18.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Shimomitsukuri {下箕作}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.22,0:12:22.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In January of the previous year,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.18,0:12:25.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda went to Shimoda \Nto preach to the local community.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.86,0:12:24.99,Top,,0,0,0,,Here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.62,0:12:29.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In just a year, the number of affiliated households had increased to 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.62,0:12:27.23,Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, Honda-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.85,0:12:32.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,One by one, the wedges Toda drove into their souls
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.91,0:12:36.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,blossomed into merit and virtue, applied in their everyday lives. {unsure: 戸田の打ったくさびが一つ一つ 功徳の体験となって 花開いてきたのである}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.74,0:12:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.57,0:12:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all turned out just as you said!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.80,0:12:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My health has become much stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.84,0:12:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can peddle my wares again \Nalmost as well as when I was young!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.51,0:12:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.14,0:12:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And with the increase in sales, \NI've even been able to start saving.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.00,0:12:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe it all to your religious guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.56,0:13:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You have my deepest gratitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.82,0:13:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, you shouldn't thank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.71,0:13:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of your admirable piety \Nthat Buddha bestowed you with strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.82,0:13:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm happy for you, Honda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.06,0:13:13.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,11 bank employees poisoned {銀行員十一名を毒殺}{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sadamichi_Hirasawa}\NGHQ public health official sent to {Shiinamachi branch of }Teikoku Bank {帝銀椎名町支店へ備防疫員}\NLeft the vault open and escaped {金庫開け放しで逃走}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.61,0:13:14.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Japan's economy was in its third year since the end of the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.52,0:13:15.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,The new budget will hurt the households \NSake costs 800 yen per sho {家計に痛い新予算\N酒は一升八百円}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.57,0:13:17.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but with inflation running rampant \Nand prices skyrocketing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.76,0:13:18.32,Sign,,0,0,0,,The bonito supply is running dry {no clue what's in the beginning or the end, ＊れ＊るカツオ入荷よすぎて＊る}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.42,0:13:19.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the economic crisis had become chronic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:23.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,100 million people were still struggling to make ends meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to your hard work,\Nwe have managed to make it this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.18,0:13:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I think about the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.78,0:13:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I realize we've reached a point where we have to take some action.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.25,0:13:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I want to start publishing a monthly magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.26,0:13:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.26,0:13:39.59,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.02,0:13:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A magazine for boys, to be precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A magazine for boys?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.10,0:13:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,For Japan's recovery, education must take precedence over everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.99,0:13:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,To which end, I believe it to be our mission to provide good books for children to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.83,0:14:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nihon Shogakkan also takes its root \Nin educational courses for children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.17,0:14:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we can inject that traditional spirit into our editing. {not sure what he means: その伝統精神は編集の上に生かせると思う \Nどうかね? - traditional here probably means that japanese culture had historically been a fusion of buddhist, confucian and shinto traditions}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.34,0:14:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.87,0:14:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.30,0:14:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All right!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.39,0:14:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.53,0:14:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.89,0:14:20.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,Adventure Boy {冒険少年}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.82,0:14:21.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus was born the boys' magazine "Adventure Boy."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.58,0:14:24.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The "Adventure Boy" quickly became a hit among children
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:28.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,for its imaginative science stories \Nand adventures in the uncharted lands {/unknown territories/terra incognita}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.20,0:14:31.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that connected to children's dreams. {/that children could relate to}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.33,0:14:36.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda devoted himself to the management of the Nihon Shogakkan,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:39.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,while at the same time training and fostering
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.02,0:14:42.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,new leaders who would handle the missionary work in various regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.04,0:14:46.07,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,New young talents emerged one after another,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:50.19,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and the banner of Lotus Sutra flew vigorously in all kinds of places.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.19,0:14:51.66,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Starting with Kamata Ward in Tokyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.66,0:14:53.71,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Tsurumi in Kanagawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.66,0:14:53.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,Tsurumi, Kanagawa Prefecture {神奈川県 鶴見}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:55.48,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Urayasu in Chiba,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:55.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,Urayasu, Chiba Prefecture {千葉県 浦安}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.18,0:14:57.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,finally, in the faraway Sendai,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.96,0:15:03.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,up-and-coming leaders were actively engaged \Nin spreading the word of Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.92,0:15:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Many young talents \Nsprouted up in Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.03,0:15:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure even more talented young people will start flocking to it from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.55,0:15:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.31,0:15:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira-kun, do you happen to know \Nif Yamamoto-kun, who joined
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.58,0:15:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,last year at Mikawa's place in Kamata, \Ndoing well these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.59,0:15:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You mean that Yamamoto-kun \Nwho had recited the impromptu poem?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.36,0:15:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Yamamoto Shinichi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.32,0:15:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I see him at roundtable talks every now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.44,0:15:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't seem to be \Nin a very good health.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.29,0:15:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.83,0:15:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason, \NI can't forget that young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.47,0:15:40.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,Kamata Station (Keihin Line) neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.99,0:15:41.34,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,At the time, Yamamoto Shinichi worked
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.34,0:15:46.07,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,as an accountant for the Jonan Kogyokai in Kamata, a private organization {城南工業会 - could translate to "Jonan Manufacturing Association"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.07,0:15:48.94,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,that subsidizes small and medium-sized enterprises.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.94,0:15:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, it's time to go to school!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.32,0:15:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.97,0:15:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you excuse me now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, we sure are lucky \Nto have you, Yamamoto-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.65,0:16:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, our paperwork is always well organized and our books are in perfect order.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.57,0:16:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What would we do without you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.21,0:16:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I don't deserve such praise.\NWell, if you excuse me leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.33,0:16:23.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,He's doing a great job hiding his condition. \NI really wish he could get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.60,0:16:29.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Taisei Academy (now Fuji Junior College), \NPolitical Science and Economics Dept., Night Classes {大世学院(現・富士短期大学)政経科\N夜間部の授業}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.33,0:16:27.63,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Eager to learn more and deepen his knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.63,0:16:30.32,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the studious and diligent young Yamamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:32.93,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,graduated from Oriental Commerce School in March
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.93,0:16:36.95,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and in April, he entered the evening class of the Political Science and Economics Department
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:39.50,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,of Daisei Academy, \Nwhere he attended classes diligently.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.50,0:16:43.39,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,In addition to pushing himself to the limit, \Nhe was anxious about his health,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:47.06,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,but the joy of learning outweighed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.06,0:16:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.42,0:16:56.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto made it his daily routine \Nto pray to Buddha and chant the sutra.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.82,0:16:59.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And whenever he was called for a roundtable discussion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.26,0:17:02.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he would try to attend on Sundays \Nas much as possible. {not sure why only on sundays}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.51,0:17:08.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He devoted as much time \Nas he could to chanting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.06,0:17:12.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As he earnestly offered the prayer, \Nhe could feel his vitality building up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.11,0:17:18.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He felt amazed at how fatigue in his body and the congestion in his chest disappeared naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.07,0:17:22.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But at the same time, in his heart of hearts, he was hesitant as to whether or not
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.23,0:17:25.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he should commit to this faith and wed his life to Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.30,0:17:33.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei is a wonderful man, \Nand I admire him with all my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.14,0:17:39.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,But the question is whether I am ready to devote my entire life to Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:44.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,If I do, that would mean my future is going to be filled with hardships,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.38,0:17:46.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,due to how great the cause of the Common Path is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.02,0:17:49.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,Will I really be able to persevere through it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.84,0:17:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.97,0:17:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.48,0:17:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. \NPlease come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.70,0:18:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nice day, Yamamoto-kun.\NWhy don't we go outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.24,0:18:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We're currently recruiting students \Nfor the 7th Lotus Sutra course of lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.24,0:18:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you join, Yamamoto-kun? \NI'll give you a recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.69,0:18:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it Toda-sensei \Nwho's giving this lecture?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.93,0:18:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.52,0:18:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei's lecture... \NI'd like to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:30.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,Investigation into Showa Denko {昭和電工を捜索 - denko could amount to "electrical engineering"}{https://time.com/archive/6601672/japan-failure/}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.99,0:18:27.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A major scandal has erupted
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.13,0:18:31.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,involving Showa Denko, a key player in the chemical fertilizer industry,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.30,0:18:34.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,Scandal reaches new stage as Vice President is accused of bribery and loan fraud {疑獄 果然新段階へ副總裁を收容融資に收賄の疑い}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.52,0:18:32.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with charges of bribery
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.82,0:18:36.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,leveled against the entire political, business, and government establishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.34,0:18:39.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It revealed how corrupt and debased \Nthe top-level politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.47,0:18:43.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,{too smudgy, ignore}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:43.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and officials who should be leading Japan were.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.48,0:18:46.83,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The people, who had high hopes for postwar democratic politics,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.83,0:18:50.38,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,were overcome with indignation and helplessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.61,0:18:51.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,Prime Minister's Residence {首相官邸}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.38,0:18:53.74,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,In the wake of this incident, \Nthe cabinet resigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.74,0:18:58.08,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, the former Prime Minister Ashida himself was arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.08,0:19:01.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,{right}Cabinet resigns today, next administration to be elected by Democratic Party of Japan {きよう内閣総辞職\N次期政権一應民自}\N{left}Appointed at the company's request {社の申入れで決意}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.46,0:19:07.27,Top,,0,0,0,,Sensei, you taught us that the root of all evil is false religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.27,0:19:11.90,Top,,0,0,0,,But how can we eradicate the kind of evil \Nlike in the Showa Denko incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.00,0:19:13.01,Sign,,0,0,0,,7th Lotus Sutra Lecture {第7期法華経講義}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.01,0:19:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an interesting question. \NLet's ponder it together tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.26,0:19:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you guys think we should do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.27,0:19:23.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda's course of lectures on the Lotus Sutra \Nconsisted of nine sessions,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.86,0:19:27.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but it was this seventh lecture that was the most lively and garnered the most attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:32.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On this day, the lecture ended early \Nand a questions session began.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.36,0:19:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Any ideas, Yoshikawa-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.36,0:19:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I believe, we have no choice but to spread the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.08,0:19:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, this time \Nthe whole thing is just too inexcusable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.37,0:19:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They take us all for fools!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.37,0:19:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if we are fighting now to eradicate these social evils...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.38,0:19:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help but think that this is the same as waiting for the cows to come home. {waiting for one hundred years for the waters of the Yellow River to clear; waiting in vain for an unlikely event - "waiting for good weather at sea," is similar in meaning, though it’s less commonly used}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:19:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"Waiting for the cows to come home?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.40,0:20:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that the grazing cows have no hope of ever finding their way home? {/that even if we waited for a hundred years, the waters of the yellow river would not become clean?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.39,0:20:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoshikawa-kun, are you saying \Nthat all hope is lost? {/want to throw in the towel​}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.86,0:20:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as for me, \NI will never stop hoping.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.86,0:20:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They secretly give or receive bribes in the form of money or goods
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.84,0:20:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to benefit themselves and only themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.87,0:20:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Social evils like this one, the bribery,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.86,0:20:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,have been going on for thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.89,0:20:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much for as long
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.43,0:20:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as the human society exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.01,0:20:31.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,Edo Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.91,0:20:34.59,Top,,0,0,0,,Many a good-hearted, righteous people made determined attempts to eradicate this evil
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.02,0:20:37.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,The "Kyoho Reforms" by the eighth shogun, Tokugawa Yoshimune, during the Edo period {江戸時代\N八代将軍・徳川吉宗による「享保の改革」}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.59,0:20:40.53,Top,,0,0,0,,by imposing legal sanctions, providing moral education, and even reforming
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.02,0:20:43.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,The Tenpo Reforms by Senior Councilor Mizuno Tadakuni {老中・水野忠邦による「天保の改革」}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.54,0:20:43.51,Top,,0,0,0,,the established social and political structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.51,0:20:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But as the recent incident shows, \Nthe effect of all those precedents had been null.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.52,0:20:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Between then and now, \Nnothing had changed in people's minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.52,0:20:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But why is it so?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.35,0:21:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why doesn't anything seem to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.57,0:21:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Can anyone tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.58,0:21:07.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,He's here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.05,0:21:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears nobody is ready \Nto answer that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.52,0:21:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let {\i1}me{\i0} tell you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.43,0:21:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason for that is because the human greed is limitless,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.73,0:21:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and it only ever keeps growing deeper and bigger, like an insatiable whirlpool.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.72,0:21:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Materialistic desires,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,desire for power,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,desire to dominate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.27,0:21:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, we are also becoming more and more indiscriminate
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.77,0:21:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in choosing the means for obtaining our goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.36,0:21:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, be it society or politics, \Nit's just ordinary people who serve as its gears. {/make it work}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.92,0:21:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you think happens when a human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.59,0:21:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,ruled by desire, \Nsits at the center of all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.26,0:21:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing good, that's for sure. {/terrifying things}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.06,0:21:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone can lament that society is bad, \Npolitics are bad, the list goes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.81,0:21:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But we won't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.52,0:21:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we must always think ahead - what can we do to eliminate and rectify these evils?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.67,0:22:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's what I want to tell you:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.62,0:22:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Society, politics, and so forth\Nall originate from the human soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.26,0:22:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If it emanates from life, then it's the man himself who must change first.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.66,0:22:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of letting your desires drag you down,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.37,0:22:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,learning to exert control over them \Nis what we must aspire for.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.97,0:22:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about making it our heart's desire \Nto work and serve the people in good faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.29,0:22:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about reforming our view of life. {/perspective/dimension}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.22,0:22:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,From a revolution of thought to human revolution. And we can do that! {unsure what he means by "circumstances; one's situation or lot in life"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.45,0:22:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It is only possible through Nichiren Daishonin's great philosophy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.34,0:22:43.08,Top,,0,0,0,,Right now, there are people in Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.08,0:22:47.35,Top,,0,0,0,,who are calling for a political revolution, and a social revolution. But as you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.35,0:22:49.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,French Revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.03,0:22:49.47,Top,,0,0,0,,in the French Revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.47,0:22:51.30,Top,,0,0,0,,Russian Revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.47,0:22:51.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,Russian Revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.30,0:22:54.37,Top,,0,0,0,,or even our homegrown Meiji Restoration,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.81,0:22:57.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,Meiji Restoration Reforms {明治維新の改革}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.37,0:22:56.65,Top,,0,0,0,,weren't they all bloody revolutions,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.65,0:23:00.94,Top,,0,0,0,,in which millions of precious lives were sacrificed to the millstone of civil strife? {lit: by force of arms}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.65,0:23:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What we need now is a religious revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.05,0:23:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Namely, a bloodless, peaceful revolution, grounded in hearing and being heard, {actually "speech and dialogue" but since it's basically the same thing i went for more abstract}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.84,0:23:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which places the sanctity of life above all, \Nas taught by the Buddha Dharma.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.83,0:23:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the foundation for that religious revolution is the human revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.33,0:23:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The transformation of life itself \Nwithin a single human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.46,0:23:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, it's a human revolution \Nthat happens in each and every one of you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.94,0:23:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's part and parcel of religious revolution, \Nand it's where everything starts.{act. just says "it's the basis" doesn't say of what}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.72,0:23:34.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,A human revolution \Nin each and every one...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.77,0:23:36.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.45,0:23:39.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's the end of my indecision. {/All my doubts are dispelled now}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.54,0:23:42.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei is inseparable from Soka Gakkai. {/... is one with ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.08,0:23:45.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll follow him decisively, \Nno matter where he leads us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.78,0:23:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For my own human revolution... {/to achieve ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.33,0:23:55.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On this night, Yamamoto Shinichi wrote the following in his diary
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.47,0:24:07.13,Sign,,0,0,0,,Ah... I have encountered the profound and infinite truth of the Lotus Sutra, and now I know that I am blessed.\NToda-sensei truly is the teacher of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.13,0:24:12.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,A world in turmoil. {I didn't forget "is" he's writing in a philosophical style}\NWho will absolve society and people? {/purify}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.71,0:24:18.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,The mission of Soka Gakkai is crucial. \NOnly if Soka Gakkai makes steady progress, will it succeed. {unsure: 学会の使命重大なり。学会の前進のみ、それを決せん。}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.77,0:24:22.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,Young man, proceed with great compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.99,0:24:26.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,Young man, arm yourself with the great philosophy. {lit: fight with ... in mind}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.14,0:24:35.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,I, at the tender age of twenty, have discovered the way to spend your youth most gloriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.26,0:24:41.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi was still just an nameless member of the Young Men's Division,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.12,0:24:46.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,who hadn't had a chance to speak directly with Toda ever since he decided to join last summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.36,0:24:51.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, Toda's aspirations took root in Yamamoto Shinichi's mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.28,0:24:53.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and blossomed into a force of their own. {/began growing}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.32,0:24:56.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto {plaque}\NTwo months later {sign}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.70,0:24:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.38,0:25:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it looking for your health these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.85,0:25:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Save for the occasional congestion, \NI'm feeling good lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.36,0:25:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even working is a lot easier for me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.70,0:25:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.86,0:25:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, remember I mentioned to you that we're looking for an editor the other day? {for a magazine }
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.47,0:25:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, it was for Toda-sensei's Nihon Shogakkan.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.49,0:25:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Toda-sensei's magazine?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.96,0:25:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He said you should write your resume \Nand come in for an interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.11,0:25:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that sound? {/what'll you do?}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.66,0:25:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I don't know if I'm the kind of person Toda-sensei is looking for,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.85,0:25:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but I should at least \Ntake a shot at this interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.59,0:25:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor said I won't even live to 26,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.08,0:25:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so I might not have all that much time left...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.11,0:25:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Great Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.41,0:25:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,please allow me to live this life
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.55,0:26:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as fully as a human being can, even if it's just for a short while. {lit: please grant me the ultimate/perfect life}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.45,0:26:06.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The next day, after the Lotus Sutra lecture was over...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.46,0:26:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.40,0:26:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.80,0:26:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, keep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.29,0:26:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I will. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.59,0:26:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.57,0:26:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.06,0:26:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought Yamamoto-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.80,0:26:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Yamamoto Shinichi. \NMy resume. {actually "nice to meet you" but they met before}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.08,0:26:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.54,0:26:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.62,0:26:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, wanna do some good? {unsure}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.63,0:26:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! You can count on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.09,0:26:50.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,I've finally crossed the Rubicon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.69,0:26:51.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.07,0:26:55.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,I am prepared to give it my all \Nand never regret it! {lit: bet my life on it - probably means "devote the rest of my life to this"}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.05,0:26:59.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That was a moment of sheer determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.76,0:27:05.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He felt like Caesar, who crossed the Rubicon and conquered Rome with a cry "The die is cast!"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.87,0:27:09.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi had also just crossed into a fateful moment {using the same verb as "cross [river rubicon]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.47,0:27:13.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that would decide \Nthe course of his entire life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.85,0:27:16.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,Twenty years old, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.51,0:27:20.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was also this age \Nwhen I first met Makiguchi-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.54,0:27:26.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,Whenever I see this young man, \NI'm reminded vividly of Makiguchi-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.83,0:27:28.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.77,0:27:33.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we are both on a mission \Nto carry on Makiguchi-sensei's legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.22,0:27:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to leave your current position \Nand come work for me. {says "retire amicably" probably means "and stay on good terms with your boss" but idk how to convey it in english}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.90,0:27:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.77,0:27:49.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The people were entering the fourth year of their lives after the war had ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.21,0:27:51.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but under the iron boot of the occupying forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.50,0:27:56.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,they were still forced to endure a life of destitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.77,0:27:59.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,New Year's Eve {大晦日ー}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.28,0:28:05.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Looking back at the past year of fighting through it all, Toda had no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.41,0:28:12.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Instead, in this moment of peace, he was looking forward to the start of the new year.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.88,0:28:14.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the same time...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.80,0:28:20.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,Today, this year ends. \NA lot has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.47,0:28:26.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,Next year, I will finally be working at Toda-sensei's magazine. I must do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.98,0:28:32.56,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,At daybreak on January 3rd, 1949...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.98,0:28:30.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,January 3rd, 1949 \NSuidobashi Station {1949年(昭和24年)1月3日\N水道橋駅}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.21,0:28:36.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's it. \NToday is my first day at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.28,0:28:41.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,I will work under Toda-sensei \Nfor the rest of my life with no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.30,0:28:46.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,To do that, I need to live each day to the fullest, as if I could drop dead the very next moment. {lit: so that I could say I could collapse any moment - his way of saying carpe diem}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.00,0:28:50.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right... \NLet's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.50,0:28:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, allow me to introduce Yamamoto-kun, who will be working here with us from today on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.37,0:28:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, please come forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.00,0:29:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.76,0:29:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun is going to be editing "Adventure Boy" for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.78,0:29:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sato-kun, can I trust you with taking good care of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.55,0:29:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.52,0:29:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, time for self-introduction, \NYamamoto-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.25,0:29:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.41,0:29:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Yamamoto Shinichi. \NI'll be working with you from today onwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.82,0:29:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no experience editing magazines, so I'm very anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.68,0:29:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But I promise to do my best \Nlearning from all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.04,0:29:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take care of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.97,0:29:44.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, a day after his 21st birthday, \NYamamoto Shinichi put his entire life on the line,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.53,0:29:47.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,both publicly and privately,{unsure what they meant by this}\N to forge ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.56,0:29:52.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,towards the accomplishment of Common Path \Nin unison with Josei Toda, {/become one with Toda Josei and walk the Common Path together - it's more a philosophical idea than a road, so...}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.50,0:29:58.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,determined to persevere through \Nall the hardships that may lie ahead...
